<font color="#FF0000">JESUS A LA KING!</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec 10 19:10:41 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
If we were all to attend a wonderful buffet laden with every imaginable type of delicious offerings and deserts, would it be fair for me to dictate what you should partake of and what you should not? No!<br>
Should I force you to eat a lot or conversely, come away hungry? No!<br>
It would not be rude of me to suggest.  Nor, would it be improper to warn that something is too hot or spicey (in accordance with my prefrences) or fattening etc.  But still I would be compelled to allow everyone to choose for themselves.<br>
I recommend that people have a spirituality that can serve them in times of need.<br>
I recognize that people must eat or perish, but I shall not be the judge of what they eat or how much!  And, I feel the same about God!...the religions of the world offer enough to choose from...just watch out for the tummy aches and learn as you go!<br><br>
MTF<br><br>

